#Text=Do you think you will be able to cover future expenses such as radio and television ads ?
#Text=Following the raid on the Pirate Bay , and our tripling of the member roster , we do n't need advertising .
#Text=We 've been mentioned almost every news hour across all channels on national television in the last week .
#Text=Also , the established parties have now started to turn , following our success .
#Text=Parties representing almost half of the elected parliament are now describing today 's copyright situation as not working .
#Text=They still do n't understand why , though , they are just echoing what we say without understanding what the words mean .
#Text=We 'll get around to teaching them — them and the voters alike .
#Text=This might be hard for people not following the Swedish media to grasp , but we have made a big splash .

#Text=Today , our Minister of Justice was quoted as saying that he 's open to changes to copyright laws that would make file-sharing legal , with the headline " Bodström ( his name ) flip-flops about file sharing . "

column1: #Text=Immediately underneath were the Pirate Party 's comments to his suggestions .
#Text=Let 's take that again : when a minister makes a statement about file sharing , media calls us for comments , and publishes them next to that statement .
#Text=That 's how big we have become since the raid on the Pirate Bay .
#Text=The Minister of Justice later denied having made that statement to the press that reported it .
#Text=We will never be able to pay for television ads , the way I see it .
#Text=Unless a very wealthy donor comes on stage .
#Text=( If any such person is reading this , we have planned how to spend up to $ 375,000 in a cost-efficient way up until the elections , on the chance that donations appear .
#Text=That spending does still not include any TV ads . )
#Text=Are you aware of similar initiatives in other countries ?
#Text=Some are trying , but none have achieved the necessary momentum and critical mass that we have .
#Text=We expect that momentum to happen once we get into Swedish Parliament and show that it can be done .
#Text=[ Ed . :
#Text=A United States variant of the party was recently launched .
#Text=See also : Intellectual property activism category on Wikipedia ]
#Text=The name " Pirate Party " seems to identify the party with what is currently defined as a crime : piracy of software , movies , music , and so on .

column1: #Text=How about potential allies abroad who argue for a more balanced copyright regime , such as the Electronic Frontier Foundation or Creative Commons ?
#Text=Oh , it is a crime .
#Text=That 's the heart of the problem !
#Text=The very problem is that something that 20 % of the voters are doing is illegal by punishment of jail time .
#Text=That 's what we want to change .
#Text=Where the established parties are saying that the voters are broken , we are saying it 's the law that is broken .
